---
description: Opinionated Angular best-practice rules with a focus on inline templates, Tailwind CSS, modern TypeScript, standalone components, signals, and performance.
globs: ["**/*.{ts,css}"]
---

# Angular Best Practices (Inline Templates + Tailwind)

This project emphasizes **inline templates** and **Tailwind CSS** for fast, consistent development while maintaining performance, accessibility, and scalability.

## TypeScript Best Practices

- **Strict Type Checking:** Keep `strict` on.
- **Prefer Type Inference:** Let TS infer when obvious.
  - **Bad:**
    ```ts
    let name: string = 'Angular';
    ```
  - **Good:**
    ```ts
    let name = 'Angular';
    ```
- **Avoid `any`:** Prefer `unknown` and narrow properly.

## Angular Best Practices

- **Standalone Only:** Use standalone components, directives, and pipes. Avoid `NgModules` for new/refactored code.
- **Implicit Standalone:** You don’t need `standalone: true`; it’s implied.
  - **Bad:**
    ```ts
    @Component({ standalone: true })
    export class MyComponent {}
    ```
  - **Good:**
    ```ts
    @Component({})
    export class MyComponent {}
    ```
- **Signals:** Use Angular Signals for reactive state in components/services.
- **Lazy Loading:** Lazy-load feature routes.
- **NgOptimizedImage:** Use for all static images.
- **Host Bindings:** Use the `host` object; **do not** use `@HostBinding` / `@HostListener`.

## Components

- **Single Responsibility:** Small, focused components.
- **Inline Templates (Default):** Use `template` and (optionally) `styles` inline.
  - **Example (inline + Tailwind):**
    ```ts
    import { ChangeDetectionStrategy, Component, computed, input, output, signal } from '@angular/core';

    @Component({
      selector: 'og-card',
      changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
      template: `
        <section class="rounded-xl border p-4 shadow-sm bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900">
          <header class="mb-2 flex items-center justify-between">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">{{ title() }}</h2>
            <button
              type="button"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-md border px-2 py-1 text-sm hover:bg-zinc-100 dark:hover:bg-zinc-800"
              (click)="refresh.emit()"
            >
              Refresh
            </button>
          </header>

          @if (loading()) {
            <p class="animate-pulse text-sm text-zinc-500">Loading…</p>
          } @else {
            <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
              <ng-content />
            </div>
          }
        </section>
      `,
    })
    export class OgCardComponent {
      title = input.required<string>();
      refresh = output<void>();
      loading = signal(false);
      // Example derived state
      upper = computed(() => this.title().toUpperCase());
    }
    ```
- **Inputs/Outputs:** Prefer `input()` / `output()` over decorators.
- **Derived State:** Use `computed()`.
- **Change Detection:** Always set `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`.
- **Reactive Forms:** Prefer Reactive Forms for anything non-trivial.

## Tailwind CSS Guidelines

- **Utilities First:** Prefer Tailwind utility classes for layout, spacing, typography, and state. Avoid per-component SCSS when utilities suffice.
- **Semantic Grouping:** Order classes roughly: layout → box-model → typography → effects → states (`hover:`/`focus:`) → responsive (`sm:`…).
- **Avoid `ngClass`/`ngStyle` when possible:** Use native `class` and `style` bindings.
  - **Bad:**
    ```html
    <section [ngClass]="{'active': isActive}"></section>
    ```
  - **Good:**
    ```html
    <section [class.active]="isActive" class="p-4 rounded-lg"></section>
    ```
- **Design Tokens via Tailwind Config:** Define theme colors, spacing, and fonts in `tailwind.config.js` rather than ad-hoc CSS.
- **Minimal CSS Files:** Use global `styles.css` for base resets and rare `@layer components` abstractions; avoid deep component-level CSS unless necessary.
- **Use `@apply` Sparingly:** Only to extract repeated patterns that aren’t components yet.

### Tailwind Setup (reference)

- `styles.css`
  ```css
  @tailwind base;
  @tailwind components;
  @tailwind utilities;

  /* Optional: global tweaks */
  html, body { @apply h-full bg-zinc-50 text-zinc-900 dark:bg-zinc-950 dark:text-zinc-100; }
  ```
- `tailwind.config.js`
  ```js
  /** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
  module.exports = {
    content: ["./src/**/*.{html,ts}"],
    darkMode: 'media', // or 'class'
    theme: { extend: {} },
    plugins: [require('@tailwindcss/typography'), require('@tailwindcss/forms')],
  };
  ```

## State Management

- **Local State:** Signals.
- **Derived:** `computed()`.
- **Pure Updates:** No side effects in transforms.
- **No `mutate`:** Use `set`/`update`.

## Templates

- **Keep Simple:** Move logic to TS.
- **Native Control Flow:** Prefer `@if`, `@for`, `@switch`.
  - **Old:**
    ```html
    <section *ngIf="isVisible">Content</section>
    ```
  - **New (inline):**
    ```ts
    template: `
      @if (isVisible()) {
        <section class="p-4">Content</section>
      }
      @for (item of items(); track item.id) {
        <div class="py-1">{{ item.name }}</div>
      }
    `
    ```
- **Async Pipe:** Use `| async` when binding Observables in templates; prefer converting to signals in TS when practical.

## Services

- **Single Responsibility:** One clear purpose.
- **`providedIn: 'root'`:** Singleton + tree-shakable.
- **`inject()` Function:** Prefer over constructor injection, especially in computed/standalone contexts.
  - **Example:**
    ```ts
    import { inject, Injectable, signal } from '@angular/core';

    @Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })
    export class PhotosService {
      private http = inject(HttpClient);
      photos = signal<Photo[]>([]);

      load() {
        this.http.get<Photo[]>('/api/photos').subscribe(this.photos.set);
      }
    }
    ```
